2 and 4, Π and Τ are crossed by slanting bars, which could indicate an abbreviation. Small H and Ο above Τ and Π at l. 4, small curved signs at the upper right of T at l. 2, T and Ν at l. 4. Small curved signs below Υ and inside Ω and Α at l. 2, which could be now decoration marks, now abbreviation marks.",[59,68],{"type":60,"l":61,"from":62,"to":63,"h":64,"unit":65,"atLeast":66,"atMost":67},"letterHeight","Lines 1-4","line1","line4","33-37","mm","33","37",{"type":69,"l":70,"from":62,"to":71,"h":72,"unit":65},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2","not recorded",{"_":74,"notBefore":75,"notAfter":76},"6th — 9 century CE",501,900,[78,83],{"_":79,"type":80,"ref":81,"region":82},"Catina","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462270","Sicilia",{"_":84,"type":85,"ref":86,"region":82},"Catania","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525068",[88],[89,90],37.49223,15.07041,{"_":92,"type":93,"subtype":94,"notAfter":95,"geo":19},"Original discovery not recorded, but probably from Catania; Tardìa, Cod. Bibl. Comunale Palermo Qq C 17 a, f. 136r mentions the inscription as coming from Catania, communicated to him by Torremuzza 21 November 1766.","found","discovered","1766-11-21",[],{"_":98,"type":99,"geo":19},"Observed by Libertini in Museo Biscari, later by Korhonen in Magazzino superiore, Collezione Biscari (formerly sala VII 288).","observed",[101],{"n":102,"url":103,"height":104,"width":105,"desc":106,"surfaceType":107},"screen","ISic003289_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana","front","Sicily",{"_":110,"role":111,"ref":112,"museum":113},"Museo Civico di Catania","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/018",{"slug":114,"type":111,"name":110,"uri":112,"description":115,"location":116},"018","Antiquarian collection, comprehensive in scope",{"settlement":84,"region":84,"country":117,"address":118,"geo":1